1. *Džepu* nedostaje dugme. (The *pocket* is missing a button.)
2. U *džepu* nosim telefon. (I carry my phone in my *pocket*.)
3. Izgubio sam novčanik u *džepu*. (I lost my wallet in my *pocket*.)
4. Kada vozim, ključeve držim u *džepu*. (When I drive, I keep my keys in my *pocket*.)
5. Stavila sam ruku u *džep* i izvukla novčić. (I put my hand in my *pocket* and pulled out a coin.)
6. *Džepovi* na ovoj jakni su preveliki. (The *pockets* on this jacket are too big.)
7. Želim da mi se *džepovi* puni novcem. (I want my *pockets* to be full of money.)
8. *Džeparenje* je učestali problem u gradskom prevozu. (*Pickpocketing* is a common problem on public transport.)
9. On je *džeparoš* i stalno krade stvari iz džepova ljudima. (He is a *pickpocket* and constantly steals things from people's pockets.)
10. Pukla mi je pantalonica na *džepu*. (The seam on the *pocket* of my pants has torn.)